<table border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=1 width=600>	<tr><td colspan=1 align=center>	<img src="/images/bar.jpg" alt="Copyright" width="500" height="22">	<br>	</td></tr>	<tr><td colspan=1 align=left>	<center>	<A HREF="employee.phtml?person=dharris" TARGET="employee"  onClick="window.open('empoyee.phtml?person=dharris', 'employee', ' scrollbars=no,status=yes,resizable=yes,width=500,height=300')"><img src="/images/smdharris.jpg" width="183" height="132" border="0" align="left"></A>	</center>	<font size="-1" face="Arial"><p><b>We'd like to introduce you to one of the Ampace Team Members, Dannie Harris, and welcome you to come <A HREF="/company/indexa.html" onMouseover="window.status='Click NOW to come inside';return true;">inside</A> to learn more about the Ampace Vision. <p><br>	<B>Dannie Harris, Driver</B><br>	(Click on Image to bring up an Enlargement)	</font>	</td></tr>	<tr><td colspan=1 align=left>	<P>	<font size="-1" face="Arial"><b>	One of Our Movers and Shakers at MDX!	<p>	MDX, based in Monroe, La., is Ampace’s <a href="/goto.phtml?dir=services&filename=intro.html">long-haul, truckload division</a> that handles freight movements in the Southeast, Central and Midwest United States. MDX became part of Ampace in 1995, and recently underwent restructuring to improve performance and gain cost efficiencies. Those tweaks to the MDX operations have paid off with an on-time performance average of 98 percent and a much-improved profit line.	<p>	Dannie Harris is one of MDX’s <a href="/goto.phtml?dir=career&filename=driverapp.html">over-the-road drivers</a>. He says he is proud to drive for MDX because of the way the company works to satisfy both its customers and drivers.	<p>	As a truck driver, Dannie knows that many in his profession have to spend several weeks away from their families. That’s not the case at MDX. "They listen to your needs and get you home when you want.  MDX has given me a stable life at home," Danny explained, adding that he rests easier knowing the company has consistent, profitable freight.	<p>	Dannie believes MDX’s future is bright and offers him stability. "It eases my mind to know that MDX’s and Ampace’s management has a good, solid understanding of the trucking industry. They not only care about our business, but the people who work here. For me personally, that means I don’t have to worry about finding another job."	</td></tr></table>
